# Code style

- Prefer function declarations; arrows only for short callbacks.
- Suffix names by role: `authMiddleware`, `usersService`, `usersController`.
- Controllers: one per request; take `context`; wire services + providers.
- Domain services: flat `services/*.service.ts`.
- Providers only: `providers/<name>/` uses `index.ts` with
  `export default` for the impl plus one named type re-export of the
  provider contract from `<name>.types.ts` (no helper input/result
  types), and `*.provider.ts` impl. Wire with
  `import AIProvider from '@/providers/ai'`; type deps/mocks with
  `import type { AIProvider } from '@/providers/ai'`. Do not use this
  default-export pattern for services, controllers, repositories, or
  middleware — those keep named exports.
- File order: imports → exports. One-class helpers: `private`
  methods. Module-level helpers only when shared across exports
  (at bottom).
- Web: split long Tailwind via `cn(...)`; use `renderBody` (or descriptive
  names) instead of nested ternaries for loading/error/empty/data.
